Rohit Sharma is an Indian cricketer. He is a right-handed batsman and a right-arm off-spin bowler. He is the vice-captain of the Indian cricket team. He is the only Indian cricketer to have scored a double century in ODI cricket.

## Early life

Rohit Sharma was born on 30 April 1987 in Mumbai, Maharashtra. He is the son of a businessman, Ashok Sharma. He has a younger brother, Vishal Sharma. He is a Hindu.

## Career

### Domestic career

Rohit Sharma made his first-class debut for Mumbai in the 2005–06 Ranji Trophy. He made his List A debut for Mumbai in the 2005–06 Vijay Hazare Trophy. He made his Twenty20 debut for Mumbai in the 2006–07 Indian T20 League on 20 January 2007.

He taught at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem from 1959 to 1968, and at the University of British Columbia from 1968 to 1972. BiographieAutres informations

## Biographie

Tilda Swinton est née le 5 novembre 1960 à Londres. Elle est la fille de Roger Swinton, un ancien pilote de chasse, et de Judith Balfour, une écrivaine. Elle a un frère, Sandy, et une sœur, Katherine.

She was a member of the Constituent Assembly. She was a member of the Lok Sabha. She was the President of the Congress Party. She was the Prime Minister of India from 1966 to 1977. She was the Prime Minister of India from 1980 to 1984. She was assassinated on 31st October 1984.

input: Write a short biography of Olivia Colman.

OLIVIA COLMAN

BY

MARY H. WILSON

AUTHOR OF "THE LIFE OF MRS. SIDNEY SMITH," "THE LIFE OF MRS. GEORGE SAND," ETC.

LONDON: TINSLEY BROTHERS, 18, CATHERINE STREET, STRAND.

1882.

[_The Right of Translation is reserved._]

PREFACE.

The following pages are intended to give a short sketch of the life of Olivia Colman, the actress, and to show how she has risen from the position of a poor girl, who was obliged to earn her living by teaching, to that of a lady of fortune, who has been able to indulge her taste for theatricals, and to enjoy the society of the most distinguished men and women of the day.

The writer has endeavoured to give a faithful account of the life of the actress, and to avoid all that is merely personal, or of a merely ephemeral character.

M. H. W.

CONT
